<div id="comment_64135493" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64135493" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64135493" name="comment_link_64135493" href="//apple.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23183627&amp;cid=64135493" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64135493)" >Just wait a year</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64135493" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64135493); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>4</a>, Interesting)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~dgatwood">dgatwood</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~dgatwood">( 11270 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64135493">		
		on Friday January 05, 2024 @08:48PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//apple.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23183627&amp;cid=64135493">#64135493</a>)
		<small><a href="http://www.shellscriptgames.com/" title="http://www.shellscriptgames.com/" class="user_homepage_display">Homepage</a>
<a href="//slashdot.org/~dgatwood/journal/" title="Friday July 17, 2009 @12:37AM" class="user_journal_display">Journal</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64135493">
<p>It won't be long before both the <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/01/05/technology/antitrust-apple-lawsuit-us.html" title="nytimes.com">U.S.</a> [nytimes.com] and the <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/commission/presscorner/detail/en/ip_23_1217" title="europa.eu">EU</a> [europa.eu] crack down on Apple's bulls**t and force them to open up the platform to both third-party app stores and third-party payment systems.  The whole Apple-in-app-purchase-only thing has always been a very flagrant abuse of their market power to drive up the cost of goods and services, and it's amazing how long the convicted monopolist has gotten away with it, but all signs point towards them paying the piper soon-ish.</p><p>As a stockholder, I cringe at how much money I'm going to lose in my stock portfolio when it happens, but forcing Apple's hand is still the right thing to do.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64135493">
